@startuml Overall System Flowchart Based on ERD

start

:User accesses system;

:User registers account;
note right: Store in User table

:User logs in;
note right: Authenticate via User table

if (User role is Admin?) then (yes)
  :Admin dashboard;
  note right: Access admin functions
  :Choose action: Manage Users, Announcements, Pets, Requests;
  if (Manage Users) then (yes)
    :CRUD operations on User table;
  elseif (Manage Announcements) then (yes)
    :CRUD operations on Announcement table;
  elseif (Manage Pets) then (yes)
    :CRUD operations on Pet table;
    :Update pet status;
  elseif (Manage Requests) then (yes)
    :Update PetRequest table;
    :Approve/Reject requests;
    :Notify users;
  endif
else (no)
  :User dashboard;
  note right: Access user functions
  :Choose action: View Pets, Create Poster, Submit Request, Manage Registration;
  if (View Pets) then (yes)
    :Retrieve visible pets from Pet table;
    :Display pet list;
  elseif (Create Poster) then (yes)
    :Store poster data in Poster table;
  elseif (Submit Request) then (yes)
    :Store request in PetRequest table;
    :Link to Pet if applicable;
  elseif (Manage Registration) then (yes)
    :CRUD on PetRegistration table for user's pets;
  endif
endif

:Data interactions via relationships;
note right: All tables linked via foreign keys

stop

@enduml
